  "visual": {
    "visualType": "textbox",
    "objects": {
      "general": [
        {
          "properties": {
            "paragraphs": [
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Instructions:",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "14pt"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "There are two options to use this template."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Option 1)",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontWeight": "bold"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": " If you already have your data on Power BI."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "\tIf you already have an SM (Semantic Model) with your data on it, the steps are:"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": " Create measures in your SM following the format of the measures of this report. The most \"format-sensitive\" measure is \"KPI Card - Example Measure (Text Arrow Card)\".                                                                   \t\t     It is good practice to use a \"@Measures\" to have all measures in. If you want to know how to create it: "
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "3.2.6. Usage of a @Measures auxiliary table - Business Intelligence - Mingle",
                    "textStyle": {},
                    "url": "https://mingle.axpo.com/spaces/BI/pages/613500964/3.2.6.+Usage+of+a+Measures+auxiliary+table"
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "                                                                                                                                           It is also suggested that you use the public calendar table in Databricks as part of your SM. Why to use it and where to find it: "
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "3.1.2. Why to use a Calendar Table - Business Intelligence - Mingle",
                    "textStyle": {},
                    "url": "https://mingle.axpo.com/spaces/BI/pages/471679082/3.1.2.+Why+to+use+a+Calendar+Table"
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet",
                "indent": 1
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": " Once you have all your measures done and published, delete all tables on this report (on the right, on the Data pane. Right-click, then \"delete from model\")."
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet",
                "indent": 1
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": " Delete all pages but \"Empty KPI Card Design\" (copy this instructions somewhere before deleting this page! And also the color codes!). Rename the page fittingly."
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet",
                "indent": 1
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": " On the top pane, on Home, click \"Get Data\" and then \"Power BI semantic models\". Select your SM (needs to be published in a Workspace)."
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet",
                "indent": 1
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": " Drag your measures to the visuals. Add new visuals if needed. Make your page longer if needed, but not wider."
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet",
                "indent": 1
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Option 2) ",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontWeight": "bold"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "If you don't have your data, the recommendation is that you do that separately, and then come back to Option 1."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "If you need guidance on how to get your data, this Mingle page is a nice place to start: "
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "1.2. Connecting to data - Business Intelligence - Mingle",
                    "textStyle": {},
                    "url": "https://mingle.axpo.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=471679012&spaceKey=BI&title=1.2.%2BConnecting%2Bto%2Bdata"
                  },
                  {
                    "value": " "
                  }
                ],
                "indent": 2
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "While you can always import your data here, to this report, the best practice is that you first do your SM model separately, and then connect the template to it after publishing. "
                  }
                ],
                "indent": 2
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
